From: Ghaf contributors <ghaf@tii.ae>
Subject: [PATCH] dce passthrough: core notifier plain WRITE, never WRITE_AWAKEN

The awaken rides the DCE async event path the guest cannot receive, and
the R5 aborts the whole completion write when the awaken cannot be
delivered -- core channel completions never land and every modeset times
out. nvkms polls the notifier memory anyway, so plain WRITE suffices.
---
diff --git a/nvdisplay/src/nvidia-modeset/src/nvkms-evo3.c b/nvdisplay/src/nvidia-modeset/src/nvkms-evo3.c
index 529ec40..dec6c95 100644
--- a/nvdisplay/src/nvidia-modeset/src/nvkms-evo3.c
+++ b/nvdisplay/src/nvidia-modeset/src/nvkms-evo3.c
@@ -3229,9 +3229,13 @@ void nvEvoSetNotifierC3(NVDevEvoRec *pDevEvo,
      */
     ASSERT_DRF_NUM(C37D, _SET_NOTIFIER_CONTROL, _OFFSET, notifier);
 
-    ctrlVal = (awaken ?
-               DRF_DEF(C37D, _SET_NOTIFIER_CONTROL, _MODE, _WRITE_AWAKEN) :
-               DRF_DEF(C37D, _SET_NOTIFIER_CONTROL, _MODE, _WRITE));
+    /* DCE host-proxy passthrough: force plain WRITE, never WRITE_AWAKEN.
+     * The awaken rides the DCE async event path the guest cannot receive,
+     * and the R5 aborts the whole completion write when the awaken cannot
+     * be delivered. nvkms polls the notifier memory anyway, so the awaken
+     * is not needed for the wait to succeed. */
+    (void)awaken;
+    ctrlVal = DRF_DEF(C37D, _SET_NOTIFIER_CONTROL, _MODE, _WRITE);
     ctrlVal |= (notify ?
                 DRF_DEF(C37D, _SET_NOTIFIER_CONTROL, _NOTIFY, _ENABLE) :
                 DRF_DEF(C37D, _SET_NOTIFIER_CONTROL, _NOTIFY, _DISABLE));
